General Install {{{1

Pip {{{2 

* Recommended by python-guide.org
easy_install3.4 pip
easy_install3.4 --user pip

* Debian Packages:
Install python-pip, python-virtualenv, and optional virtualenvwrapper
Debian package of pip - no python3

VirtualEnv Wrapper: Also could install with pip with optional install to .local
pip install virtualenvwrapper --install-option="--user"

*  Pip Manual
curl -O https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
sudo python get-pip.py  # system wide
sudo python get-pip.py --user # local 
Run pip install with python3 to get pip3

Includes setuptools


pipenv {{{2
https://www.kennethreitz.org/essays/announcing-pipenv

pip install pipenv


Virtualenv  {{{2

sudo pip install virtualenv #system wide
pip install --user virtualenv #local to .local/bin
Virtualenv installed with pip3 will default to python3 or virtualenv --python=/usr/bin/python3 --no-site-packages

3. Virtualenvwrapper
Must install to same location as virtualenv
During install will look for first python and virtualenv on PATH

